subject: Re: [junit] Comparing JTest and JUnit
msgSnippet: Jtest automatically generates tests (and can export the generated tests to a JUnit class), whereas JUnit is a framework for you to put in tests and run them. I
messageBody:
Jtest automatically generates tests (and can export the generated tests to a JUnit class), whereas JUnit is a framework for you to put in tests and run them. I don't think these two tools are comparable.

Tao
